rest_of_day_open: It will be great. My husband is off tomorrow so we will go on a breakfast date while my son is in school. We will have a quick workout session and sweat. His family is coming into town this weekend so it will be interesting to see the dynamic. I have one more work day.
critical_positive: We both were excited to keep it going. We brought up different subjects and kept relating to one another. I did feel I spoke more than her, but she was happily listening. Her camera did go out so it was a bit weird towards the end because it felt as if though I was talking to myself.
critical_negative: I was doing the majority of the talking. I feel like I need to fill any silence. I speak really fast and felt bad because I kept taking over the conversation. She didn't seem to mind and loved asking questions about me and why I did things. She seemed to enjoy learning more about me.

rest_of_day_open: In a little bit of a slump as the holidays approach and the weather gets colder, but I'm not able to see many of my friends or family. I see the rest of the week passing pretty slowly as I get my stuff done. Hopefully I can find something to look forward to.
critical_positive: My partner was extremely enthusiastic, comfortable, and talked a lot. We didn't have many awkward pauses because she would transition from topic to topic on her own, and I only had to prompt or offer questions once in a while. She was also open about her issues and I felt like I knew her based on what she was saying.
critical_negative: I was already feeling a little bit low energy going into the conversation, so I felt somewhat disconnected as she talked and I listened. When she talked for extended periods of time, I felt myself losing focus or attention and only being able to ask questions about specific phrases I heard and remembered.
